      "blocks": {
        "story_eyebrow": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Our story",
            "size": "sm",
            "uppercase": true,
            "muted": true
          }
        },
        "story_heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Why we started Uplink.",
            "size": "3xl"
          }
        },
        "story_body": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We spent a decade inside larger MSPs where every ticket bounced between three engineers and nobody owned the outcome. Office managers were the ones left on hold, translating between techs and their own frustrated staff.</p><p>Uplink is the version of that model we wish had existed — small named teams, published pricing, documentation the client actually owns. Run the way we'd want our own family's business to be run.</p>",
            "size": "base",
            "uppercase": false,
            "muted": false
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["story_eyebrow", "story_heading", "story_body"]
    },
